    <note>Xu(3) Churen [745] His sons moved to Raozhou, Poyang xian at the beginning of the Southern Song. Chen(1) Xiang's [47] son-in-law, Kang's [758], Keng's [760] and Du's [3382] father. His son-in-law, Mao(1) Bing [3673], was the son of Mao(1) You [3674], a Quzhou, Jiangshan resident and probably kin of Mao(1) Jian [1356] and Mao (1) Yan [1358]. SHY:SH, 56.2a-2b, 33a; SS, 371.2a; Wang Zao, WJ, 28.20b (wife, surname Chen(1), who died in 1123 at age 54). CBD, 3, 2034.</note>
